Frank SWEENEY et al., Appellants, v. STATE BOARD OF PUBLIC ASSISTANCE, Appellee. No. 7682. Circuit Court of Appeals, Third Circuit. May 28, 1941. See, also, 36 F.Supp. 973. Frank Sweeney, of Alden, Pa., for himself. Joseph F. Tedesco, of Scranton, Pa. (M. Louise Rutherford, Deputy Atty. Gen., and Claude T. Reno, Atty. Gen., on the brief), for defendant.

Before BIGGS, CLARK, and JONES, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The judgment of the court below is affirmed.
